. *===============================================================================
. * Section 4.2.1: Primary Data Entry
. *===============================================================================
. 
. *----------------------------------------------------------------
. * Simple data entry using input command
. *----------------------------------------------------------------
. 
. clear all

. 
. input variable_x variable_y variable_z

     variabl~x  variabl~y  variabl~z
  1. 31 57 18
  2. 25 68 12
  3. 35 60 13
  4. 38 59 17
  5. 30 59 15
  6. end

. 
. * Display the data
. list

     +--------------------------------+
     | variab~x   variab~y   variab~z |
     |--------------------------------|
  1. |       31         57         18 |
  2. |       25         68         12 |
  3. |       35         60         13 |
  4. |       38         59         17 |
  5. |       30         59         15 |
     +--------------------------------+

. 
. * Save the dataset
. save "Example_1_0.dta", replace
file Example_1_0.dta saved

. 
. * To enter additional data using Stata editor
. * edit
. 
. * Export to CSV format
. export delimited using "Example_1.csv", replace
file Example_1.csv saved

